# Purpose
The purpose of this file is to list all user stories that will be used to help program the solution for sprint 1, and plan ahead for future sprints.

# Sara Adi's User Stories:
Title: Course Information
Priority: High
Estimate (in hrs): -
User Story:
As a student, I want to be able to access all the undergraduate course information easily, so that I can plan my course selection efficiently. I expect to find this information in the application.
Acceptance Criteria:
- I can access undergraduate course information within the application.
- All existing prerequisites are visible and correlate to their predetermined courses.
- The course information is complete and up-to-date.

Title: Search Courses
Priority: Medium
Estimate (in hrs): -
User Story:
As a student, I want to have the option to search for specific courses or information within the application, so that I can quickly find the courses I'm interested in without navigating through the entire list.
Acceptance Criteria:
- I can use a search feature within the application to find courses or information.
- The search feature works efficiently and accurately.


# Simardeep Singh's User Stories:
Title: Save and Export Recommendations
Priority: Medium
Estimate (in hrs): -
User Story:
As a student, I want the option to save and export the course recommendations generated by the Excel VBA application to a separate file, such as PDF or Excel, so that I can refer to them later and share them with advisors or peers.
Acceptance Criteria: 
- A feature is added to save and export course recommendations.
- Users can choose the file format (pdf, excel, etc.) for saving.
- The saved/exported recommendations are accurate and well formatted.

Title: Course Recommendation Button
Priority: High
Estimate (in hrs):
User Story:
As a student, I want a clearly visible and easily accessible button within the Excel VBA application that I can click to receive course recommendations for the next semester based on my completed courses and prerequisites.
Acceptance Criteria:
- A custom button is added to the Excel spreadsheet.
- When the button is clicked, the application triggers the course recommendation algorithm.
- The spreadsheet updates with recommended courses based on prerequisites.

Title: Multiple OS Compatibilty
Priority: Low
Estimate (in hours):
User Story: As a student, I want the application (CLI) to run across or be compatible with different operaing systems, so that I can use it regardless of my platform.
Acceptance Criteria:
- The Python CLI program runs smoothly on different operating systems.
- Students can perform searches on the course data without platform specific issues.

# Emily Kozatchiner's User Stories:
Title: Course List
Priority: High
Estimate (in hrs): -
User Story: As an undergraduate student, I want to view all course prerequisites required for courses of my choice.
Acceptance Criteria:
- Verify that the prerequisites shown for a course entered is correct
- Verify that if a course has no prerequisites, the CLI will inform the user
- Verify that users can choose other courses after intial choice

#Fee Kim's User Stories

Title: Course Validator
Priority: - Low
Estimate (in hrs): - 

User Story: 
As an undergraduate student, I want that the Excel spreadsheet automatically validate and highlight any incorrectly entered 
course names to ensure accuracy.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Verify that the user can easily see if the course code/name has been incorrectly entered.
- Verify that the user can easily correct the incorrect course name/codes by suggesting possible correct names/codes.

